/* <orly/lang_tests/general/variants_destructure.orly>

   End-to-end test for issue #95 Phase 3 M4 (variant destructuring): the
   two Option-A surface features, proven against a stored, read-back
   variant.

     1. `e is <Tag>` predicate -> bool. True iff the active arm of the
        variant `e` is `<Tag>`. Mirrors the optional `is known` family.
        Lowers to `(e).GetWhich() == <idx>`, where `<idx>` is the
        asciibetical index of `<Tag>` in the variant's tag set (the order
        the generated native struct's `Which` follows).

     2. `e.<Tag>` guarded payload accessor -> the `<Tag>` arm's declared
        payload type. Reuses the `e.field` (postfix_obj_member) surface,
        disambiguated from record field access by the operand type at
        type-check time. Lowers to `(e).GetV<Tag>()`, which asserts the
        active arm is `<Tag>` -- so it is normally gated by `e is <Tag>`,
        exactly as the example below does.

   The variant value is read back from storage (the M2 `::(T)`-driven
   sabot read-back), so this proves destructuring works on a genuinely
   round-tripped value, not just a freshly-constructed one.

   Copyright 2010-2026 Atomic Kismet Company

   Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");
   you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.
   You may obtain a copy of the License at

     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

   Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software
   distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,
   WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.
   See the License for the specific language governing permissions and
   limitations under the License. */

read_var = (*<[n]>::(<| Integer(int) | Deleted |>)) where {
  n = given::(int);
};

/* Typed arm: predicate selects the active arm; the guarded accessor
   extracts its payload. */
with {
  <[400]> <- <| Integer(int) | Deleted |>.Integer(7);
} test {
  t_isA: read_var(.n: 400) is Integer == true;
  t_isB: read_var(.n: 400) is Deleted == false;
  /* not over the predicate works (it is a plain bool). */
  t_notB: not (read_var(.n: 400) is Deleted);
  /* Guarded payload extraction: gated by the predicate, so GetVInteger()
     is only reached when the active arm really is Integer. */
  t_pay: (read_var(.n: 400).Integer if read_var(.n: 400) is Integer else 0) == 7;
};

/* Tag-only arm: predicate selects Deleted; the Integer accessor is gated
   off (its predicate is false), so the conditional takes the else branch
   and the asserting GetVInteger() is never evaluated. */
with {
  <[401]> <- <| Integer(int) | Deleted |>.Deleted;
} test {
  t_isC: read_var(.n: 401) is Deleted == true;
  t_isD: read_var(.n: 401) is Integer == false;
  t_payD: (read_var(.n: 401).Integer if read_var(.n: 401) is Integer else -1) == -1;
};
